lead_paragraph: Scott Gutschewski shot a five-under-par 67 yesterday at PGA West to take a one-stroke lead over Jeff Gallagher and Ryan Howison after the first round of the PGA Tour’s 108-hole final qualifying tournament in La Quinta, Calif. Gutschewski had six birdies and one bogey in 30-mile-an-hour gusts on the Jack Nicklaus Tournament Course. The top 30 and ties after six rounds will receive 2007 PGA Tour cards.
